headline: CPC LOGISTICS DRIVERS JOIN TEAMSTERS
summary: CPC Logistics drivers in Joliet, Ill., have voted to unionize with Teamsters Local 179. The group of 42 workers transport products for major companies like John Deere, Procter & Gamble, and Walgreens. They are seeking higher wages, improved benefits, and protection from at-will employment.

headline: Zefiro Methane Subsidiary Begins Work on its Second-Largest Orphan Well Project Valued at Approximately USD $4.5 Million
summary: Zefiro subsidiary Plants & Goodwin, Inc. is currently plugging 37 wells in Wood County, Ohio as part of the scope of work for Wood 12F, an orphan well project that is expected to generate approximately USD $4.5 million in revenue. headline: Tide Evo Launch Tests Procter And Gamble Growth And Sustainability Story
summary: Procter & Gamble (NYSE:PG) has launched Tide evo, a waterless detergent tile, as part of a nationwide rollout. The product is highly concentrated, designed to work in cold water, and aims to reduce packaging waste. Tide evo represents a new laundry format that Procter & Gamble reports took a decade to develop. headline: Nestle plans sale of ice cream business as fourth-quarter sales growth beats estimates
summary: Nestle shares rose 3% Thursday after the maker of Nescafé and KitKat reported organic sales growth for the fourth quarter that beat analyst forecasts.
